<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> singular form <i>pilli</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.britannica.com/eb/topic-460561/pilli" class="external text" title="http://www.britannica.com/eb/topic-460561/pilli" rel="nofollow">pilli (Aztec social class)</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-Noguera-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Noguera_17-0" title="">^</a></b> <i>Annals of Anthropology</i>, UNAM, Vol. xi, 1974, p. 56</li>
<li id="cite_note-Sanders-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Sanders_18-0" title="">^</a></b> Sanders, William T., <i>Settlement Patterns in Central Mexico. Handbook of Middle American Indians</i>, 1971, vol. 3, p. 3-44.</li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.bvashram.org/articles/82/1/Why-varnashrama-is-only-in-India%3F" class="external text" title="http://www.bvashram.org/articles/82/1/Why-varnashrama-is-only-in-India%3F" rel="nofollow">Why varnashrama is only in India?</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-US_Census_Bureau.2C_personal_income_distribution.2C_age_25.2B.2C_2006-20">^ <a href="#cite_ref-US_Census_Bureau.2C_personal_income_distribution.2C_age_25.2B.2C_2006_20-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-US_Census_Bureau.2C_personal_income_distribution.2C_age_25.2B.2C_2006_20-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-US_Census_Bureau.2C_personal_income_distribution.2C_age_25.2B.2C_2006_20-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-US_Census_Bureau.2C_personal_income_distribution.2C_age_25.2B.2C_2006_20-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/perinc/new03_001.htm" class="external text" title="http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/perinc/new03_001.htm" rel="nofollow">"US Census Bureau, personal income distribution, age 25+, 2006"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/perinc/new03_001.htm" class="external free" title="http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/perinc/new03_001.htm" rel="nofollow">http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/perinc/new03_001.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-12-28</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=US+Census+Bureau%2C+personal+income+distribution%2C+age+25%2B%2C+2006&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fpubdb3.census.gov%2Fmacro%2F032006%2Fperinc%2Fnew03_001.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Social_class"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://student.britannica.com/comptons/article-208190/social-class" class="external text" title="http://student.britannica.com/comptons/article-208190/social-class" rel="nofollow">"Encyclopedia Britannica"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://student.britannica.com/comptons/article-208190/social-class" class="external free" title="http://student.britannica.com/comptons/article-208190/social-class" rel="nofollow">http://student.britannica.com/comptons/article-208190/social-class</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-04-07</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+Britannica&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fstudent.britannica.com%2Fcomptons%2Farticle-208190%2Fsocial-class&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Social_class"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Occupation_and_Class_Consciousness_in_America-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Occupation_and_Class_Consciousness_in_America_22-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFEichar1989">Eichar, Douglas (1989). <i>Occupation and Class Consciousness in America</i>. Westport, Connecticut: Greenwood Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0313261113" class="internal">ISBN 0-313-26111-3</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Occupation+and+Class+Consciousness+in+America&amp;rft.aulast=Eichar&amp;rft.aufirst=Douglas&amp;rft.au=Eichar%2C+Douglas&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.place=Westport%2C+Connecticut&amp;rft.pub=Greenwood+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-313-26111-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Social_class"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Middle_income_can.27t_buy_Middle_class_lifestyle-23">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Middle_income_can.27t_buy_Middle_class_lifestyle_23-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Middle_income_can.27t_buy_Middle_class_lifestyle_23-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.news.harvard.edu/gazette/2003/10.30/19-bankruptcy.html" class="external text" title="http://www.news.harvard.edu/gazette/2003/10.30/19-bankruptcy.html" rel="nofollow">"Middle income can't buy Middle class lifestyle"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.news.harvard.edu/gazette/2003/10.30/19-bankruptcy.html" class="external free" title="http://www.news.harvard.edu/gazette/2003/10.30/19-bankruptcy.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.news.harvard.edu/gazette/2003/10.30/19-bankruptcy.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-12-28</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Middle+income+can%27t+buy+Middle+class+lifestyle&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.news.harvard.edu%2Fgazette%2F2003%2F10.30%2F19-bankruptcy.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Social_class"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-The_American_Perception_of_Class-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-The_American_Perception_of_Class_24-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFVannemanLynn_Weber_Cannon1988">Vanneman, Reeve; Lynn Weber Cannon (1988). <i>The American Perception of Class</i>. New York, NY: Temple University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0877225931" class="internal">ISBN 0877225931</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+American+Perception+of+Class&amp;rft.aulast=Vanneman&amp;rft.aufirst=Reeve&amp;rft.au=Vanneman%2C+Reeve&amp;rft.au=Lynn+Weber+Cannon&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+NY&amp;rft.pub=Temple+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0877225931&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Social_class"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> The two critera, and class consciousness determines action, are from Evans, p 80.</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> The classes are: "bureaucrats and theocrats in the Asiatic mode of production; freemen, slaves, plebians, and patricians under slavery; lord, serf, guild master and journeyman under feudalism; industrial capitalists, financial capitalists, landlords, peasantry, petty bourgeoisie, and wage labourers under capitalism." Elster, p 124.</li>
<li id="cite_note-The_American_Class_Structure-27">^ <a href="#cite_ref-The_American_Class_Structure_27-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_American_Class_Structure_27-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_American_Class_Structure_27-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_American_Class_Structure_27-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_American_Class_Structure_27-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-The_American_Class_Structure_27-5" title=""><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGilbert1998">Gilbert, Dennis (1998). <i>The American Class Structure</i>. New York: Wadsworth Publishing. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0534505201" class="internal">ISBN 0-534-50520-1</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+American+Class+Structure&amp;rft.aulast=Gilbert&amp;rft.aufirst=Dennis&amp;rft.au=Gilbert%2C+Dennis&amp;rft.date=1998&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Wadsworth+Publishing&amp;rft.isbn=0-534-50520-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Social_class"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-US_Census_Bureau.2C_overall_household_income_distribution.2C_2006-28">^ <a href="#cite_ref-US_Census_Bureau.2C_overall_household_income_distribution.2C_2006_28-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-US_Census_Bureau.2C_overall_household_income_distribution.2C_2006_28-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-US_Census_Bureau.2C_overall_household_income_distribution.2C_2006_28-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-US_Census_Bureau.2C_overall_household_income_distribution.2C_2006_28-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/hhinc/new06_000.htm" class="external text" title="http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/hhinc/new06_000.htm" rel="nofollow">"US Census Bureau, overall household income distribution, 2006"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/hhinc/new06_000.htm" class="external free" title="http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/hhinc/new06_000.htm" rel="nofollow">http://pubdb3.census.gov/macro/032006/hhinc/new06_000.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-12-28</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=US+Census+Bureau%2C+overall+household+income+distribution%2C+2006&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fpubdb3.census.gov%2Fmacro%2F032006%2Fhhinc%2Fnew06_000.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Social_class"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
